WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.940
Okay, so today I'm going to talk about a first-in-class anti-CD94 antibody. DR01 was

00:00:06.940 --> 00:00:12.380
the previous name, and recently we got a new name, Dibodatug, and this is in relapsed refractory

00:00:12.380 --> 00:00:23.440
cytotoxic lymphomas. So cytotoxic NK and T-cell lymphomas are a rare group of malignancies,

00:00:23.800 --> 00:00:29.640
and they have a high admit need. In non-Hodgkin lymphoma, they make up less than 15% of all

00:00:29.640 --> 00:00:36.280
non-Hodgkin lymphomas. These cytotoxic lymphoma entities, and these include extranodal NK T-cell

00:00:36.280 --> 00:00:42.460
lymphoma, the intestinal lymphomas, hepatosplenic T-cell lymphomas, subcutaneous paniculitis-like

00:00:42.460 --> 00:00:49.140
T-cell lymphoma, or primary cutaneous gamma-delta T-cell lymphoma, they are characterized by a

00:00:49.140 --> 00:00:55.340
cytotoxic phenotype and commonly expressed CD94. These patients have very poor prognosis,

00:00:55.740 --> 00:00:59.280
and there is really no standard of care treatment approach for these

00:00:59.280 --> 00:01:03.440
patients. The median overall survival is generally less than one year from diagnosis,

00:01:04.200 --> 00:01:07.440
and this highlights a significant unmet medical need.

00:01:09.680 --> 00:01:18.060
So Dibodatug, or DR01, is a non-fucosylated IgG antibody that is expressed on terminal

00:01:18.060 --> 00:01:26.140
effector CD8-positive T-subsets and NK cells. So you can see here on the left, CD94 expression

00:01:26.140 --> 00:01:28.400
is minimal to absent on naive.

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:36.100
And a memory subsets, but it's quite high in terminal effector and natural killer populations,

00:01:36.100 --> 00:01:42.340
and that provides for a degree of biologic selectivity. Dibodatug engages the FC gamma

00:01:42.340 --> 00:01:50.500
receptors, such as CD16A, and triggers ADCC, and this results in rapid depletion of CD94 expression

00:01:50.500 --> 00:01:59.120
from terminal effector cells. So this is a first in human open-label phase 1-2,

00:01:59.120 --> 00:02:05.720
study looking at the safety and preliminary efficacy of Dibodatug in relapsed refractory

00:02:05.720 --> 00:02:12.520
cytotoxic T-cell lymphomas. There was several phases to this study. Essentially, the part A

00:02:12.520 --> 00:02:18.920
was dose escalation, and the doses ranged anywhere from 0.3 milligrams per kilogram up to 10 milligrams

00:02:18.920 --> 00:02:26.900
per kilogram with both CTL, so cytotoxic T-lymphomas, and LGLL patients treated at those

00:02:26.900 --> 00:02:27.460
doses. Part B was dose escalation, and the doses ranged anywhere from 0.3 milligrams per kilogram up to 10 milligrams per kilogram with both CTL, so cytotoxic T-lymphomas, and LGLL patients treated at those doses.

00:02:27.460 --> 00:02:28.020
Part B was dose escalation, and the doses ranged anywhere from 0.3 milligrams per kilogram up to 10 milligrams per kilogram with both CTL, so cytotoxic T-lymphomas, and LGLL patients treated at those doses.

00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:34.220
Part B was just dose optimization and dose expansion, and there we actually see we have

00:02:34.220 --> 00:02:43.400
separate cohorts for the CTL and the LGLL populations. The optimal dose for the CTL

00:02:43.400 --> 00:02:47.180
patients have been determined, and it was determined to be 1 milligram per kilogram.

00:02:47.540 --> 00:02:52.580
There's been several induction regimens that are still being looked at for these patients,

00:02:52.580 --> 00:02:57.860
but overall, the induction is during the first month. After that, it's just once every

00:02:57.860 --> 00:03:06.800
four weeks, so here we see the baseline demographics. The median age is 53 years.

00:03:06.800 --> 00:03:12.340
Most of the patients were non-Hispanic whites. To date, the most common histology that is

00:03:12.340 --> 00:03:19.300
represented here include extranodal NKT cell lymphoma at 24% and primocutaneous gamma-delta

00:03:19.300 --> 00:03:27.700
T cell lymphoma at 20%. Number of prior lines of therapy was 3. 41% of patients were refractory

00:03:27.700 --> 00:03:33.380
to their prior therapy, and 16% of patients had prior stem cell transplant.

00:03:35.460 --> 00:03:45.240
Here is the AE table, and slide of the 81 cytotoxic T cell lymphoma patients who were

00:03:45.240 --> 00:03:51.380
treated. Infusion-related reactions was the most common treatment-related AE. The majority were

00:03:51.380 --> 00:03:56.980
low-grade, and all events were manageable with mitigation of the standard monoclonal

00:03:57.540 --> 00:04:02.180
antibody strategies that we use, such as pre-medication, splitting the initial dose over

00:04:02.180 --> 00:04:09.620
two days, etc. There were five cases of viral infections or reactivations noted as well. They

00:04:09.620 --> 00:04:15.540
were as well all low-grade, and they all result as expected, and there were no treatment-related deaths

00:04:15.540 --> 00:04:27.380
observed. So here we see efficacy of the Bota tug and overall response rates 53%, CR rate 30%, and

00:04:27.380 --> 00:04:37.380
a CR rate of 60%. We can see the POTUS-Plenic T cell lymphoma with an overall response rate of 75%

00:04:37.380 --> 00:04:45.540
and a CR rate of 50%, SPT-CL an overall response rate of 80%, and a CR rate of 60%. I mean,

00:04:46.740 --> 00:04:49.700
I think we all know these are diseases that, generally, if you have them,

00:04:51.140 --> 00:04:56.740
it's essentially equivalent to a death sentence for a majority of our patients. Here we see the

00:04:56.740 --> 00:04:57.220
SWIM-LANE T cell lymphoma with an overall response rate of 75% and a CR rate of 80%.

00:04:57.220 --> 00:04:57.460
Here we see the SWIM-LANE T cell lymphoma with an overall response rate of 80%. Here we see the

00:04:57.460 --> 00:04:57.780
SWIM-LANE T cell lymphoma with an overall response rate of 75% and a CR rate of 80%. Here we see the

00:04:57.780 --> 00:04:58.100
SWIM-LANE T cell lymphoma with an overall response rate of 75% and a CR rate of 80%. Here we see the

00:04:58.100 --> 00:04:58.500
SWIM-LANE T cell lymphoma with an overall response rate of 75% and a CR rate of 80%. Here we see the

00:04:58.500 --> 00:05:04.420
patients who received the one milligram per kilogram dose, and we are seeing durable responses. The

00:05:04.420 --> 00:05:12.900
median duration of response is 9.9 months, and the longest duration on treatment to date is 27 months

00:05:12.900 --> 00:05:23.300
and is ongoing. So, biomarker analysis showed that CD94 expression was found on 95% of the baseline

00:05:23.300 --> 00:05:25.300
tumor samples, but the clinical responses were observed on 95% of the baseline tumor samples, but

00:05:25.300 --> 00:05:26.500
the clinical responses were observed on 95% of the baseline tumor samples, but the clinical responses

00:05:26.500 --> 00:05:28.020
were observed on 95% of the baseline tumor samples, but the clinical responses were observed independent

00:05:28.020 --> 00:05:34.580
of baseline CD94 expression level, and the CD94 positive cells were depleted with Dabotatug.

00:05:36.900 --> 00:05:42.740
So, to conclude, Dabotatug continues to demonstrate promising safety and efficacy,

00:05:42.740 --> 00:05:50.100
supporting its development as a treatment option in cytotoxic T cell lymphomas. In terms of safety,

00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:55.140
infusion-related reactions was really the most common. Treatment-related AE usually occurred during

00:05:55.140 --> 00:06:01.140
the first dose and was manageable with standard mitigation strategies. Overall response rates

00:06:01.140 --> 00:06:07.860
were very promising, 53%, and there were a high proportion of CRs across multiple histologies as

00:06:07.860 --> 00:06:13.140
well. The responses were durable with a median duration of response of close to 10 months.

00:06:13.700 --> 00:06:19.780
CD94 expression was near universal across all these samples, but, you know, when we

00:06:19.780 --> 00:06:24.980
did the analysis, patients did benefit from Dabotatug regardless of their baseline CD94

00:06:24.980 --> 00:06:32.180
expression level. This study is currently ongoing. There is a phase two, and it's enrolling CTL

00:06:32.180 --> 00:06:39.220
patients globally. And these are all the sites that are involved and all the investigators, so

00:06:39.220 --> 00:06:41.380
thank you everybody.
